{"id":1320049292,"question_id":2846,"lang":"cpp","lang_name":"C++","time":"1 week, 6 days","timestamp":1720900840,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"228 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1320049292/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Robot Collisions","memory":"195.1 MB","code":"class Solution {\npublic:\n    vector<int> survivedRobotsHealths(vector<int>& positions, vector<int>& healths, string directions) {\n        int n = positions.size();\n        vector<int> index(n);\n        for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {\n            index[i] = i;\n        }\n        sort(index.begin(), index.end(), [&](int i, int j){\n            return positions[i] < positions[j];\n        });\n        stack<int> s;\n        for (auto i : index) {\n            if (directions[i] == 'R') {\n                s.push(i);\n                continue;\n            }\n            while (!s.empty() and healths[i] > 0) {\n                int j = s.top();\n                s.pop();\n                if (healths[i] > healths[j]) {\n                    healths[i]--;\n                    healths[j] = 0;\n                } else if (healths[i] < healths[j]) {\n                    healths[i] = 0;\n                    healths[j]--;\n                    s.push(j);\n                } else {\n                    healths[i] = 0;\n                    healths[j] = 0;\n                }\n            }\n        }\n        vector<int> ans;\n        for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {\n            if (healths[i] > 0) {\n                ans.push_back(healths[i]);\n            }\n        }\n        return ans;\n    }\n};","compare_result":"","title_slug":"robot-collisions","has_notes":true,"flag_type":1}
